---
import Section from "../shared/Section.astro";
import Card from "../shared/Card.astro";
---

<section class="project-explanation py-20 bg-black">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-12 text-center">
            What is Nextla?
        </h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div class="card-container">
                <div class="card bg-black p-8 rounded-lg border border-navy">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">The Project</h3>
                    <p class="text-white mb-4">
                        Nextla presents ServiceNow and software asset management concepts
                        through an engaging narrative framework. By exploring technical
                        ideas through character-driven stories, we make complex systems
                        more accessible.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-300">
                        The project bridges technical documentation with creative
                        storytelling, offering parallel paths to understanding the same
                        core concepts.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card-container md:mt-12">
                <div class="card bg-black p-8 rounded-lg border border-jade">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-jade mb-4">The Name</h3>
                    <p class="text-white mb-4">
                        "Nextla" draws inspiration from Mesoamerican culture, referencing
                        both "next" (future) and elements of Aztec terminology. This
                        connection highlights the project's exploration of value systems,
                        attention economics, and the relationship between technology and
                        humanity.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-300">
                        The Mesoamerican influence extends through visual motifs,
                        organizational structures, and symbolic elements throughout the
                        project.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
